HEADWORD: Shellfish
<hw>Shell"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any aquatic animal whose external covering consists of a shell,
either testaceous, as in oysters, clams, and other mollusks, or
crustaceous, as in lobsters and crabs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shelling</ent>⟦br⟧
